race.comment: Tricky race and very wary of a couple of first starters, namely WATTO'S MARK, who trialled very well and will pay to watch the market closely. BUSTER BIFF (2) resumed from a break at Pinjarra and bombed the start. Was always well back, then wide throughout, and ran a race far better it looks. Fitter and can improve out of sight here. CORACAO (9) resumed here at 1100m and found the line strongly. Fitter again and can run on into the finish. TWO TIME CHARLIE (1) is a big chance as he resumes for a new yard. This is far easier than debut in a hot form race at Belmont Park and after a solid trial should run well this level. DAISIESFORTHELADYS (8) is a four start maiden who has been thereabouts and will strip fitter for the fresh-up fourth. Drawn for a good run. SAFEDEEL (3) is a former Canberra galloper resuming after almost a year off for the new yard. Placed in a recent trial and should be running on hard.
